<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="344" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="35.[132,777,929,1009]" pageId="35" pageNumber="344">DERIVATIO NOMINIS. — Refers to the bright outer rim of these fairly thick circular coccoliths (luminus = light, canthus = ‘rim of the wheel’), when viewed in cross-polarized light.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="344" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="35.[131,775,1034,1171]" pageId="35" pageNumber="344">
DIAGNOSIS. — This new genus is erected to include circular coccoliths consisting of a non-perforated, practically closed, central disk and a much smaller outer rim with many slightly bent elements (n&gt; 30). The outer rim is always highly birefringent in cross-polarized light, the central disk sometimes (e.g. in the 
<typeStatus box="[565,607,1147,1171]" pageId="35" pageNumber="344">type</typeStatus>
species).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="344" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="35.[130,777,1209,1736]" box="[132,262,1209,1235]" pageId="35" pageNumber="344">DISCUSSION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[130,777,1209,1736]" pageId="35" pageNumber="344">
Four species are currently included in this genus (in stratigraphical order): 
<taxonomicName box="[249,400,1275,1301]" class="Prymnesiophyceae" family="Coccolithaceae" genus="Luminocanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Coccosphaerales" pageId="35" pageNumber="344" phylum="Haptophyta" rank="species" species="eolutetiensis" status="n. gen., n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[249,400,1275,1301]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="344">L. eolutetiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[407,555,1276,1302]" pageId="35" pageNumber="344" rank="species">n. gen., n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from the lowermost Lutetian of the Belgian Basin (see below), 
<taxonomicName box="[594,775,1309,1335]" class="Prymnesiophyceae" family="Coccolithaceae" genus="Luminocanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Coccosphaerales" pageId="35" pageNumber="344" phylum="Haptophyta" rank="species" species="plenilutetiensis" status="n. gen., n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[594,775,1309,1335]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="344">L. plenilutetiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[132,277,1343,1369]" pageId="35" pageNumber="344" rank="species">n. gen., n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from the lower middle Lutetian of the Belgian Basin and the Paris Basin (see below), 
<taxonomicName authority="(Muller, 1970)" baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[516,775,1375,1402]" class="Prymnesiophyceae" family="Coccolithaceae" genus="Luminocanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Coccosphaerales" pageId="35" pageNumber="344" phylum="Haptophyta" rank="species" species="hirsitus" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[516,615,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="344">L. hirsitus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="MULLER C." box="[629,768,1375,1402]" pageId="35" pageNumber="344" pagination="82 - 101" refId="ref42128" refString="MULLER C. 1970. - Nannoplankton aus dem Mittel-Oligozan von Norddeutschland und Belgien. Neues Jahrbuch fur Geologie und Palaontologie Abhandlungen 135 (1): 82 - 101." type="journal article" year="1970">Müller, 1970</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[130,228,1409,1435]" pageId="35" pageNumber="344" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from the lower middle Oligocene of 
<collectingCountry box="[634,725,1409,1435]" name="Belgium" pageId="35" pageNumber="344">Belgium</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[133,234,1442,1468]" name="Germany" pageId="35" pageNumber="344">Germany</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="MULLER C." box="[250,385,1442,1468]" pageId="35" pageNumber="344" pagination="82 - 101" refId="ref42128" refString="MULLER C. 1970. - Nannoplankton aus dem Mittel-Oligozan von Norddeutschland und Belgien. Neues Jahrbuch fur Geologie und Palaontologie Abhandlungen 135 (1): 82 - 101." type="journal article" year="1970">Müller 1970</bibRefCitation>
; Steurbaut 1986) and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Muller, 1970)" baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1970" class="Prymnesiophyceae" family="Coccolithaceae" genus="Luminocanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Coccosphaerales" pageId="35" pageNumber="344" phylum="Haptophyta" rank="species" species="hoerstgensis" status="n. comb">
<emphasis box="[629,775,1442,1468]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="344">L. hoerstgensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="MULLER C." box="[140,286,1476,1502]" pageId="35" pageNumber="344" pagination="82 - 101" refId="ref42128" refString="MULLER C. 1970. - Nannoplankton aus dem Mittel-Oligozan von Norddeutschland und Belgien. Neues Jahrbuch fur Geologie und Palaontologie Abhandlungen 135 (1): 82 - 101." type="journal article" year="1970">Müller, 1970</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[303,394,1476,1502]" pageId="35" pageNumber="344" rank="species">n. comb</taxonomicNameLabel>
from the upper middle Oligocene of Northern 
<collectingCountry box="[274,375,1509,1535]" name="Germany" pageId="35" pageNumber="344">Germany</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="MULLER C." box="[391,528,1509,1535]" pageId="35" pageNumber="344" pagination="82 - 101" refId="ref42128" refString="MULLER C. 1970. - Nannoplankton aus dem Mittel-Oligozan von Norddeutschland und Belgien. Neues Jahrbuch fur Geologie und Palaontologie Abhandlungen 135 (1): 82 - 101." type="journal article" year="1970">Müller 1970</bibRefCitation>
). Both Oligocene species have been synonymized with the upper Eocene species 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gartner &amp; Smith, 1967)" baseAuthorityName="Gartner &amp; Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1967" box="[134,731,1576,1603]" class="Coccolithophyceae" family="Noelaerhabdaceae" genus="Cribrocentrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Isochrysidales" pageId="35" pageNumber="344" phylum="Haptophyta" rank="species" species="reticulatum">
<emphasis box="[134,429,1576,1602]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="344">Cribrocentrum reticulatum</emphasis>
(Gartner &amp; Smith, 1967)
</taxonomicName>
(cf. Nannotax 3, http://www.mikrotax.org/Nannotax3/index. html), although erroneously, as these taxa are fundamentally different (e.g. in construction of distal shield and number of elements in the shields).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
